# Frontend (Next.js)

## Conventions

- **App Router:** routes live in `app/` (layouts and pages). Do not use Pages Router (`pages/`, `getServerSideProps`).
- Components live in `front/components/`, utilities in `front/lib/`. Use TypeScript, reusable and well-typed components.
- Styles use **Tailwind CSS v4**.

## API and Strapi

- Requests to Strapi go through `front/lib/api.ts` (or an equivalent helper). On the server use the internal Docker URL: `http://back:1337`. On the client use `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL`.
- ISR: when fetching from the API, set `next: { revalidate: 60 }` (revalidation every 60 seconds).
- Build: Next.js should use `output: 'standalone'` for Docker images.

## Example (server-side API call)

```ts
// Server Component or server action
const apiUrl = process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL ?? 'http://back:1337';
const res = await fetch(`${apiUrl}/api/...`, { next: { revalidate: 60 } });
```

## Do NOT

- Do not use `pages/`, `getStaticProps`, `getServerSideProps`.
- Do not hardcode the backend URL on the client — always use `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL`.
